        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6497.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. B. Innes, 10 December [1868]</ref> and n. 2. The animal referred to was supposed to be a hybrid of a Highland cow and a deer.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4042.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Warburton Robinson</ref>. See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6497.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. B. Innes, 10 December [1868]</ref> and n. 3.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5311.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Frederick Allen’s</ref> wife, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_7147.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Frances Allen</ref>, had complained to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin</ref> about Robinson’s conduct (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6497.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. B. Innes, 10 December [1868]</ref>).</note>
